he crossroads of art and the vernacular, challenging the distinction between canonical art photographs and the kind of output common to commercial photography studios. Boone’s account recasts our understanding not only of this celebrated figure but of photography within the arc of "idian Black life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American photographersvBiographyzUnited States. 0aAfrican American photographerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aHarlem Renaissance. 0aPhotography, Artistic. 0aPortrait photographersvBiographyzUnited States. 0aPortrait photographerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPortrait photography. 7aPhotography / Individual Photographers / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027164?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027164423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027164/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles